<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 12:39PM MDT  by NWS Pocatello</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS NEAR ELBA AND ALMO REMAINING NEARLY
STATIONARY THROUGH 130 PM MDT...
At 1236 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking two strong thunderstorms
one near Elba and the other near Almo. These storms were nearly
stationary.
HAZARD...Heavy rain, pea sized hail, and lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Watch for
enhanced runoff in otherwise dry washes and gullies.
Locations impacted include...
Almo and City of Rocks.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
